  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "There are several consistent predictors regardless of domain: men, those with higher income, and those with higher perceived technology competence were more comfortable with AI management in all three domains.",
    "Those who felt more in control of their lives (i.e., higher internal locus of control) were less comfortable with AI management in every domain.",
    "Age had no influence on participant's comfort with AI in any domain.",
    "Race and employment status showed little influence on comfort levels.",
    "Finally, education and innovativeness were not significant predictors in any of the models."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}